lkar: {{t|krc|жюзюм}}, {{t|krc|джюзюм}}\n* Karakalpak: {{t|kaa|ju'zim}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|жүзім}}\n* Khakas: {{t|kjh|виноград}}\n* Khalaj: {{t|klj|hüzüm}}, {{t|klj|angûr}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|ទំពាំងបាយជូរ}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|포도(葡萄)}}\n* Kumyk: {{t|kum|юзюм|tr=yüzüm}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|ترێ}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|tirî|m}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|жүзүм}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ອາງຸ່ນ}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|uva}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|vīnoga|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|vynuogė|f}}\n* Lombard: {{t+|lmo|uga}}, {{t+|lmo|üga}}, {{t+|lmo|uva|f}}\n* Lutuv: {{t|clt|mingsuv}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|Drauf|f}}, {{t|lb|Gron|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|грозје|n-p}}\n* Malagasy: {{t+|mg|voaloboka}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|anggur}}, {{t|ms|jabit}} (in Kelantan)\n* Malayalam: {{t+|ml|മുന്തിരി}}\n* Maltese: {{t|mt|għenba|f}}\n* Manchu: {{t|mnc|ᠮᡠᠴᡠ}}\n* Manx: {{t|gv|berrish-feeyney|f}}, {{t|gv|smeyr-feeyney|f}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|wāina}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|द्राक्ष|n}}\n* Miami: {{t|mia|aahsanteepakwi}}\n* Mi'kmaq: {{t|mic|aloqoman|in}}\n* Mingrelian: {{t|xmf|ჸურზენი}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|mn|усан үзэм|qq=Mongolia}}, {{t+|mn|үзэм|qq=China}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{t|mn|ᠤᠰᠤᠨ ᠦᠵᠦᠮ}}, {{t|mn|ᠦᠵᠦᠮ}}\n* Nahuatl:\n*: Classical Nahuatl: {{t|nci|xocomecatl}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|chʼil naʼatłʼoʼii}}\n* Nogai: {{t|nog|юзим}}, {{t|nog|юьзим}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|drue|m|f}}, {{t+|nb|vindrue|m|f}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|drue|f}}, {{t|nn|vindrue|f}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|uva|f}}, {{t+|oc|rasim|m}}\n* Odia: {{t|or|ଅଙ୍ଗୁର}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|wīnberġe|f}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|грозно|n|qq=collective}}\n* Pashto: {{t|ps|انګور|m|tr=angūr}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|انگور|tr=angur}}\n* Piedmontese: {{t|pms|uva|f}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Wiendruw|f}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|winogrono|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|uva|f}}\n* Punjabi: {{t+|pa|ਅੰਗੂਰ}}, {{t|pa|ਦਾਖ}}\n* Pwo:\n*: Western Pwo: {{t|pwo|စဘံၭ}}\n* Quapaw: {{t|qua|házi}}\n* Quechua: {{t|qu|uwa}}\n* Romani: {{t|rom|drakh|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|strugure|m}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|iva|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|виногра́дина|f}}, {{t+|ru|виногра́д|m|qq=collective}}\n* Sami:\n*: Kildin Sami: {{t|sjd|выннҍмӯррьй}}, {{t|sjd|мӯррмӯррьй}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|द्राक्षा|f}}\n* Santali: {{t+|sat|ᱚᱝᱜᱩᱨ}}\n* Sardinian: {{t|sc|úa|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|fìon-dearc|f}}, {{t|gd|dearc-fhìona|f}}, {{t|gd|fìon-dearcag|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|грозд|m}}, {{t|sh|грожђе|n-p|qq=collective}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|grozd|m}}, {{t+|sh|grožđe|n-p|qq=collective}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|racina|f}}\n* Sindhi: {{t|sd|اَنگوُرُ|m|tr=angūru}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|hrozno|n}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|grozdje|m-p}}\n* Somali: {{t+|so|canab|m}}\n* Sotho: {{t|st|morara}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|uva|f}}, {{t|es|malvasía|f|qq=very sweet}}, {{t|es|masvale|m|qq=very sweet}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|droifi}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|zabibu}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|vindruva}}, {{t+|sv|druva|c}}\n* Sylheti: {{t|syl|ꠀꠋꠉꠥꠞ}}\n* Tabasaran: {{t|tab|тӏумтӏар}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|ubas}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|ангӯр}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|திராட்சை}}\n* Taos: {{t|twf|ùboʼóna}}\n* Tarifit: {{t|rif|aḍir|m}}\n* Tashelhit: {{t|shi|ⴰⴹⵉⵍ}}\n* Tatar: {{t+|tt|йөзем}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|ద్రాక్ష}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|องุ่น}}\n* Tibetan: {{t|bo|རྒུན}}, {{t|bo|ཆུ་རྒུན་འབྲུམ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{t|ti|ወይኒ}}\n* Tongan: {{t|to|moli}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|üzüm}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|اوزوم|tr=üzüm}}, {{t|ota|انكور|tr=engûr}}, {{t|ota|عنب|tr=ʼineb}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|üzüm}}\n* Udi: {{t|udi|тӏул}}\n* Ugaritic: {{t|uga|𐎙𐎐𐎁}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|виногра́д|m}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|داکھ|f}}, {{t|ur|انگور|m|tr=aṅgūr}}\n* Uyghur: {{t+|ug|ئۈزۈم}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|uzum}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|([[trái]], [[quả]]) {{t+|vi|nho}}}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|vitidabäl}}, {{t+|vo|vitidabälem|q=collective}}\n* Wappo: {{t|wao|kóla}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|grawnwinen|f}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|umdiliya}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|טרויב|f}}, {{t|yi|ווײַנטרויב|f}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|angur}}, {{t+|zza|engur}}, {{t|zza|anggur}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|makit}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|vine|grapevine}}\n\n{{trans-top|colour}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|szőlőlila}}\n* Ido: {{t|io|vitobereo}}, {{t|io|vitobero-koloro}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|葡萄色|tr=budōiro}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|포도색(葡萄色)}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|màu}} {{t+|vi|nho}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|mawi}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|grapeshot}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj}}\n\n# Containing grapes or having a grape [[flavor]].\n# Of a [[dark]] [[purplish]] [[red]] colour.\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|flavour}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|гро́здов}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|druiven-}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|szőlős}}, {{t|hu|szőlőízű|qq=only for flavor, not contents}}\n* Ido: {{t|io|vitobera}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|[[葡萄]][[味]]|tr=budōaji}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|winogronowy|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[de]] [[uva]]}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|üzüm}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|([[vị]]) [[nho]]}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|enghur}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|colour}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|druivenkleurig}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|szőlőlila}}\n* Ido: {{t|io|vitoberea}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|d'uva}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|([[màu]]) [[nho]]}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|mewi}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# To [[pick]] grapes.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1973|author=Nancy Safford|title=Time's Island; Portraits of the Vineyard|page=35|passage=I used to go '''graping''' and blackberrying and blueberrying.}}\n# Of livestock, to develop [[tubercule]]s as a result of [[tuberculosis]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1856|author=w:House of Commons of the United Kingdom|title=Reports from Committees|page=138\n|passage=Some are called ticked; some have the milk fever; some have worm-'ith-tail ; some are '''graped''' ; others are broken-up old cows.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Public Health - Volume 4 |year=1891 |page=249 |passage=The lungs were in a bad condition, hard in places, and lumpy and badly '''graped'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Report of the Royal Commission Appointed to Inquire Into the Administrative Procedures for Controlling Danger to Man Through the Use as Food of the Meat and Milk of Tuberculous Animals |author=Great Britain Royal Commission on Tuberculosis |year=1898 |page=245 |passage=Do I understand that the carcases of the '''graped''' cows, to which you refer, were used for food ?}}\n# To develop a [[texture]] with small grape-like [[clusters]] of a [[contaminant]] or [[foreign]] [[substance]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Cuckooz Contrey |author=Kenneth Slessor |year=1932 |passage=Over the huge abraded rind, Crow-countries '''graped''' with dung, we go, Past gullies that no longer flow And wells that nobody can find, Lashed by the screaming of the crow, Stabbed by the needles of the mind.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1991|author=Desheng Li|title=Tectonic types of oil and gas basins in China|page=162\n|passage=Some small '''graped''' pisolitic textures are primary but not important.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012|author=K. Subramanian|title=Lead-free Solders: Materials Reliability for Electronics|page=169|isbn=1119966809\n|passage=An additional concern is the problem of '''graping''', which becomes more visible when type-4 solder powder is required for fine-pitch μ-BGA attachment.}}\n# {{lb|en|Northern|_|UK}} To [[grope]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1780|author=Alexander Wilson|title=A Pedlar's Story|passage=Lang, lang I sought and '''graped''' for my pack, Till night and hunger forced me to come back.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1836|author=William Stephenson Jr|title=Punch and Toby|passage=Aw '''graped''' my way out i' the dark, An' down the stairs aw scrafflel'd}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1836|author=Walter Scott|title=The antiquary|page=56\n|passage=I dinna ken,” said Steenie ; “ the book had fa'en out 0' his pocket, I fancy, for I fand it amang my feet when I was '''graping''' about to set him on his legs again, and I just pat it in my pouch to keep it safe ;}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1881|author=Robert Burns|title=The Two Lawyers|page=280\n|passage='Till in a declamation mist, His argument he tint it; He gapéd for't, he '''graped''' for't, He fand it was awa, man;}}\n# {{rfex|en}} {{lb|en|Hong Kong}} To [[envy]] ({{ng|from {{m|en|sour grapes}}}}).\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{ety|en|id=rape|text=*|:from|rape|:influence|grape<id:wine-berry>}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Internet slang|euphemistic}} {{fa sp|en|rape}}.\n#: {{syn|en|🍇}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|en\n|grapist\n}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Internet slang|euphemistic}} {{fa sp|en|rape}}.\n#: {{syn|en|🍇}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aegpr|gaper|pager|parge}}\n\n{{C|en|Fruits|Grapevines|People|Purples|Rape|Violets}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{clipping|da|grapefrugt}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|/ɡrɛjb/|[ɡ̊ʁɛjb̥]|[ɡ̊ɹɛjb̥]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|n|r}}\n\n# [[grapefruit]]\n#: {{syn|da|grapefrugt}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-noun-infl|n|r}}\n\n{{C|da|Fruits}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fi|:ubor|en:grape<id:wine-berry>}}\n{{ubor|fi|en|grape}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-p|greip|h=grape}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|fi|archaic}} {{synonym of|fi|greippi||grapefruit}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{fi-decl-nalle|grap|||a}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2026-05-14}}\n\n{{C|fi|Fruits}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|[ˈɡrape]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ro|noun form|g=f-p}}\n\n# {{noun form of|ro|grapă||indef|pl|;|indef|gen//dat|s}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|es|verb form}}\n\n# {{es-verb form of|grapar}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{clipping|sv|grapefrukt}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# [[grapefruit]]\n#: {{syn|sv|grapefrukt}}\n\n{{C|sv|Fruits}}"}}